In this posting:
[1] International trade, suggested origin of the event
[2] Spread, control measures, map 

******
[1] International trade, suggested origin of the event
Date: Sat 25 Aug 2018
Source: Caixin Net / Free Asia Radio [In Chinese, machine transl., summarised, edited]
https://hk.news.appledaily.com/china/realtime/article/20180825/58605783


African swine fever (ASF) has continued to expand in the mainland. Following Shenyang City in Liaoning province, Zhengzhou City in Henan province and Lianyungang City in Jiangsu province, the ASF epidemic has spread to Zhejiang province, where 340 pigs died on 3 farms in a breeding area in Yueqing City [see <20180823.5983494>]. Caixin.com reported yesterday [24 Aug 2018] that the source and route of ASF virus entering China is still under investigation; however, there is some evidence and opinions referring the source of the epidemic to Russia, such as genetic tests showing the sequencing results of the Chinese virus being completely consistent with the corresponding sequence of the Russian Irkutsk 2017 strain.

Several ASF epidemics have occurred in the far east of Russia since 2017. Mainland reporters found that Chinese officials have recorded a small amount of pig by-products from a pig-raising company in the Russian epidemic area this month.

In the 20 days from the beginning of this month [August 2018] to the present, the epidemic has spread from the northeastern part of China to the coastal cities of Jiangsu and Zhejiang. After the outbreak, the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Affairs sent a supervision team to Zhejiang, and launched an emergency response mechanism to take measures such as blockade, culling, and disinfection, prohibiting all pigs and susceptible animals and products from being transported into or out of the blockade area. It means that the local epidemic has been effectively controlled.

According to industry insiders, this is the beginning of the Sino-US trade war. China no longer imports US pork, due to its elevated high prices, and bought 240 000 tons of Russian pork. This seriously threatens China's pigs and the safety of the entire pig breeding industry.

According to media sources in Heilongjiang province, ASF was first discovered from the northeast and spread rapidly to the south. Now everyone thinks that trouble comes from Russia, but all departments are dismissing responsibility, and even the official news of importing Russian pigs is blocked. According to the trend of Russian live pig trade prices, starting from 14 Mar 2018, the price of live pigs in Russia has increased by 50%.

--
